From 6a42af6f64567c7011939b7c1b1e1709f5f0ab68 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ryder Lee <ryder.lee@mediatek.com>
Date: Mon, 19 Jan 2026 20:07:18 -0800
Subject: [PATCH 87/89] mtk: mt76: mt7996: add support for loading power limit
 table from file

Background:
When adding single SKU power tables for 30 or more config directly into
the MT76 device tree overlay, the resulting dtbo size exceeds 2.x MB.
This causes the system to hang at "starting kernel" during boot, likely
due to a size limitation when mounting the dtbo.

To address this, power limit tables are now loaded from a user-provided
file in the filesystem, and a debugfs knob is added for runtime control.

Users can now create a separate power limit file for each country, making
it easy to adjust settings as needed. As a result, the sku_idx mechanism
is no longer required.

Key changes:
- Add functions to read and parse power limit table from a text file.
- Support flexible parsing of 1D/2D arrays for rates and path limits.
- Apply parsed power limits to driver structures for each band/channel.
- Add debug output for easier verification of parsed values.
- Add debugfs knob 'power_table_file' to enable file-based power table.
- When enabled, re-initialize txpower and update firmware for all PHYs.
- Roll back changes if any step fails.

This enables easier testing and tuning of power limit settings without
recompiling the driver or firmware, and allows dynamic switching between
default and file-based configurations at runtime. Also avoids dtbo size
limitations and boot issues caused by large embedded power tables.

Add support for configuring the singlesku file path for mt7996 either via
the hostapd.conf or through debugfs. This enables more flexible SKU table
management and runtime adjustment.

Signed-off-by: Ryder Lee <ryder.lee@mediatek.com>
